Backend notes:
- The project now includes Vercel serverless functions under `api/`.
- `GET /api/catalog/search?provider=itunes&term=...` searches albums.
- `GET /api/catalog/album?provider=itunes&id=...` fetches album details and track lists.
- `GET /api/catalog/match?provider=itunes&title=...&artist=...` finds the best catalog match for an album and returns its tracks.
- `iTunes` works without credentials.
- `Spotify` is also supported if `SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID` and `SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET` are set in Vercel project settings.

Album syncing:
- Each album page can now sync tracks, artwork, and year from iTunes or Spotify.
- Synced catalog data is stored in browser localStorage so it appears in the app without editing `js/data.js`.
- If you import an album through the generator, the output now includes `catalog` metadata so the app can re-sync it later.

Local development:
- Install project dependencies: `npm install`
- Run the app with functions enabled: `npx vercel dev`
- Optional shortcut: `npm run vercel:dev`
- This uses the local Vercel CLI from `node_modules`, so no global install or sudo is needed.
- The existing static pages will still deploy on Vercel without a build step.